# Production coding

## Before editing

- State working assumptions, success criteria, and how you will verify (commands or runtime check).
- If requirements are ambiguous in a risky way, pause and ask or document the conservative choice.

## While editing

- Smallest diff that satisfies the task; match local style, naming, and imports.
- No drive-by refactors or unrelated formatting.
- Remove only dead code you introduced; do not delete unrelated comments or behavior.
- Prefer extending existing helpers over parallel implementations.

## Definition of done (feature-sized work)

Typed boundaries, persistence or explicit provider abstraction where state matters, validation at API/UI contract edges, user-safe errors, tests or a clearly scoped test gap with rationale, and evidence (command output or repro steps) before calling it done.

